 of some families. Degree 4 is the\nintriguing case. Here we are able to show that the singular locus of the\ngeneric member of a family of rational quartics, fixing the singularity type,\nis of linear type. We conjecture that every irreducible quartic has singular\nlocus of linear type.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 3 Jan 2011 08:18:46 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 22 Feb 2011 15:30:38 GMT"}],"update_date":"2011-02-23"}
